    "long_instructions": "## Do This:\r\n\r\n1. Add two conditionals to the `check_square(painter)` function definition:\r\n   - First, check if the `Painter` `is_on_paint()`, and if it is, then the `Painter` should `scrape_paint()`.\r\n   - Second, check if the `Painter` `can_move()`, and if it can, then the `Painter` should `move()`. \r\n2. Call the `check_square(painter)` function after the `turn_around()` function call.\r\n3. *Consider:* What can you use to continue to call the `check_square(painter)` function repeatedly so that the `Painter` scrapes up the line of paint it just put down like the image below?*\r\n4. Give your ideas a try!\r\n   - *How do `if` statements and `while` loops work together in this program? What would happen if we moved the conditionals outside the loop?*\r\n\r\n<img src=\"https://images.code.org/143dc2209f3ac15665dc9b11545bfb46-image-1738551358664.gif\" style=\"width: 200px;\"> ",
    "start_sources": {
      "files": {
        "0": {
          "id": "0",
          "name": "main.py",
          "language": "py",
          "contents": "from neighborhood import Painter\n\n# Create Painter object\nfatima = Painter()\n\n# Define paint_and_move function to collect paint, \n# Then move and paint while painter can move\n# Parameter: painter object\ndef paint_and_move(painter):\n  while fatima.is_on_bucket():\n    fatima.take_paint()\n  while fatima.can_move():\n    fatima.move() \n    fatima.paint(\"yellow\")\n\n# Define check_square function to scrape paint if painter is on paint,\n# Then move one square if painter can move\n# Parameter: painter object\ndef check_square(painter):\n  #ADD CONDITIONALS HERE\n\n  \n\n# Define turn_around function to make painter turn around\n# Parameter: painter object\ndef turn_around(painter):\n  fatima.turn_left()\n  fatima.turn_left()\n  \n# Function Calls\npaint_and_move(fatima)\nturn_around(fatima)\n#ADD CALL TO check_square(painter) FUNCTION HERE\n\n  \n",
          "folderId": "0",
          "active": true,
          "open": true
        }
      },
      "folders": {
      }
    },
